<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🎨 WD003 Week 3 — English Worksheet</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Design System — A Consistent Feel · <strong>Course:</strong> Portfolio Site · <strong>Time:</strong> about 45 minutes</p>
<p>This week you give your site a <strong>design system</strong>. You decide your colors, font, and spacing <em>once</em> — as <strong>CSS variables</strong> — and reuse them everywhere. When everything pulls from the same set of values, the whole site feels like it belongs together.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>A CSS variable is defined in <code>:root</code> with two dashes, like <code>--primary: #d4380d;</code>. You use it anywhere with <code>var(--primary)</code>. Change it in one place, and it updates everywhere.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read each block of CSS. Before you imagine the page, write what you think will happen.</p>
<pre><code class="language-css">:root {
  --primary: #d4380d;
}
h1 { color: var(--primary); }
h2 { color: var(--primary); }
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Both headings pull from <code>--primary</code>. If you change <code>--primary</code> to blue, how many headings change color?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code class="language-css">:root {
  --space-2: 16px;
  --space-4: 32px;
}
section { padding: var(--space-4); }
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What does <code>padding: var(--space-4)</code> do to the space inside each section? How much space is it?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code class="language-css">:root {
  --text: #333333;
}
body { color: var(--text); }
h1 { color: var(--primary); }
</code></pre>
<p><strong><code>--primary</code> was never defined in <code>:root</code>. What color will the <code>h1</code> be?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Spot the Bug 🐛</h2>
<p>Each block of CSS below was meant to do something, but it is broken. Read what the code is <strong>supposed</strong> to do, then rewrite it so it works. After that, explain why the original was wrong and why your fix works.</p>
<p><strong>Bug A</strong> — The body text is supposed to use the <code>--text</code> color variable, but the page shows plain black instead.</p>
<pre><code class="language-css">:root {
  --text: #333333;
}
body { color: --text; }
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> a variable name on its own is not enough — it needs to be wrapped.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug B</strong> — This is supposed to define a primary color variable, but the value is missing its proper form.</p>
<pre><code class="language-css">:root {
  primary: d4380d;
}
h1 { color: var(--primary); }
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> a CSS variable name starts with two dashes, and a hex color starts with <code>#</code>.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug C</strong> — Every section is supposed to have the same inside spacing using the spacing scale. Right now every section uses a different random number, so the page looks uneven.</p>
<pre><code class="language-css">.hero    { padding: 30px; }
.about   { padding: 18px; }
.projects{ padding: 25px; }
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> define one spacing variable and use it for all three.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why does using one spacing variable make the page look more consistent?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Build Your Design System 📸</h2>
<p>Open your site from last week and give it a design system in a <code>&lt;style&gt;</code> block.</p>
<ol>
<li>In <code>:root</code>, define <strong>three colors</strong>: <code>--primary</code>, <code>--secondary</code>, and <code>--text</code>. Pick a palette that feels like <em>you</em>.</li>
<li>Define a <strong>spacing scale</strong>: <code>--space-1</code> through <code>--space-4</code> (try 8px, 16px, 24px, 32px).</li>
<li>Apply your font to the <code>body</code> (a Google Font, or a clean default).</li>
<li>Use <code>var(--space-4)</code> for the padding on every <code>&lt;section&gt;</code> so they all match.</li>
</ol>
<p>When you finish, send a <strong>photo or video</strong> of your site with its new colors and spacing, then explain what you did. Use these sentence starters — write 4 to 6 sentences total.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The colors I chose for my variables are …</p>
<p>I picked these colors because …</p>
<p>I used <code>var(--space-4)</code> to …</p>
<p>Before the design system, my page looked …</p>
<p>After applying it, my page looked …</p>
<p>If I had more time, I would change …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Record Your Walkthrough 🎥</h2>
<p>Now take a video on your phone (or a parent's phone) while you show your styled site. Talk through it like you are teaching someone who has never used CSS variables. Try to use these words: <strong>variable</strong>, <strong>color</strong>, <strong>spacing</strong>, <strong>consistent</strong>, <strong>reuse</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Show your <code>:root</code> block and read out your color variables.</li>
<li>Change one variable's value live and show the page update everywhere.</li>
<li>Point to two sections and show their spacing matching.</li>
<li>Say why defining values once is better than repeating numbers.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write what you will say in your video.</strong> Use the space below to plan it before you record — you can read from it while filming.</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

